It's time to Put Period to U.S. Arbitrary and High-handed Practices
                         --KCNA Analyst--
 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- It is the prevailing trend of the world situation that voices critical of the U.S. bellicose foreign policy and the "anti-terror war" are growing stronger worldwide.
 The results of the midterm Congressional election in the United States in which the Democratic Party came to dominate both houses are a proper judgement meted out to the foreign policy of the present U.S. administration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the wake of the Republican defeat in the midterm election, Rumsfeld, the main player in executing the war policy of the Bush administration, was compelled to resign as secretary of Defense. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the midterm election, U.S. media unanimously called for the ouster of Rumsfeld. This was prompted by their disillusion with the Republican forces which have pursued domestic and foreign policies of aggressive, unpopular and reactionary nature which are characterized by arbitrary and high-handed practices. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Americans feel tied of bellicose Bush forces' anti-terror war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the opinion poll conducted by News Week throughout the country, the overwhelming majority of the respondents described the Iraqi war as a completely wrong war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bush, finding himself in a weak position politically in the wake of the Republican setback in the midterm election, kicked off his untimely world trip in a bid to improve the U.S. international image. This is well illustrated by his participation in the APEC Summit and his junket to Asian countries including Indonesia.  But all this went against his intention. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
. Bush suffered an unprecedented diplomatic failure in the wake of his defeat in the midterm election due to his hard-line and hostile policy towards the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Before and after the APEC Summit and his junket to Asian countries, protest against the U.S. foreign policy and "anti-terror war" further mounted in this region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bush was so cold-shouldered in Vietnam that he could not come out of the bullet-proof car but had no option but to remain seated there. People in some ten cities in Indonesia including Jakarta strongly demanded that Bush be treated as a war criminal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the facts reflect the towering indignation of the international community against the U.S. unprecedentedly high-handed and arbitrary practices and its open state terrorism, infringement upon other countries' sovereignty and human rights abuses. And they indicate that it is time to put an end to the U.S. behaviors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a historical lesson that a policy running counter to the desire of humankind is bound to meet a fiasco.

Rodong Sinmun on Anti-U.S. Struggle Gathering Force in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- The anti-U.S. struggle mounting to an ever greater crescendo among the south Korean people today proceeds from the historical lesson that they cannot think of human life and dignity, to say nothing of the country's reunification and prosperity, without terminating the U.S. policy of occupation and domination which has lasted for more than 60 years, declares Rodong Sinmun Wednesday.
 Noting that many areas of south Korea are scenes of furious rallies, protests and general strikes against the signing of the "Free Trade Agreement" with the U.S. and sanctions and blockade against the DPRK and new war provocation moves of the U.S. imperialists that gravely threaten peace of the Korean Peninsula, the author of the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-U.S. struggle of the south Korean people is a patriotic struggle of justice for defending the nation's dignity, independence and vital rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a link in the whole chain of the righteous patriotic struggle to pave the way for independent reunification through the nation's unity and cooperation under the banner of "By our nation itself," the main spirit of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people are waging the struggle to implement the joint declaration in close combination with the struggle against the U.S. and war, holding that the declaration is, immediately, the banner of independence against the U.S. and herein lies the peace and reunification of the country. Their intensive struggle demonstrates firm resolution and will to shatter the anti-peace, anti-reunification policy of the U.S imperialists hell bent on a war of aggression against the DPRK and permanent division of the Korean Peninsula and bring about a new society of national independence and a new day of reunification at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-U.S. struggle in south Korea is a confrontation between progress and conservatism, patriotism and treachery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Victory in the anti-U.S. and anti-war struggle is in store for the south Korean people fighting in close unity for peace and independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-U.S. organizations and people of all social strata in south Korea should thwart and smash the U.S. imperialists' moves to provoke a new war and hinder the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration with united strength by tightening unity and solidarity. And they should wage more gallantly the just patriotic struggle to drive the U.S. imperialist aggression forces out of south Korea.

Seminar on Kim Jong Il's Work Held in Mexico 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- A seminar on Kim Jong Il's famous work "The Workers' Party of Korea Is the Party of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung" and a film show were held by the Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism on Nov. 24.
 Present there were Ramon Jimenez Lopez, president of the committee, and members of the committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the seminar highly praised President Kim Il Sung for successfully embodying the Juche idea in the party construction and activities and Kim Jong Il for developing the WPK into the party of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the immortal feat performed by Kim Jong Il in the cause of building a revolutionary party that he systemized the President's theory on the party construction, they noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the WPK has creditably fulfilled its mission and role as the staff of the revolution, they called on the progressive parties of the world to learn from the experience gained by the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean film "The Arch of Triumph" was shown on the occasion.

Ryongchon County People's Hospital Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- The newly built Ryongchon County People's Hospital in North Phyongan Province of the DPRK was inaugurated on Nov. 28.
 The hospital having diagnosing rooms, rooms for medical treatment, sick-rooms, chambers and pharmaceutical rooms is well furnished with latest medical appliances, facilities and fixtures. The inauguration of the hospital has made it possible to more satisfactorily render services for the promotion of the health of the residents in the county and preventive and curative work for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Different countries and international bodies gave sincere assistance in the construction of the hospital. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Chang Sik, minister of Public Health, was among those present at the inaugural ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Ryon Song, chairman of the Ryongchon County People's Committee, in his inaugural speech recalled that Kim Jong Il took every possible measure to stabilize the living of the residents of the county who suffered from an accident, ensure that a helicopter was flown to bring the serious cases to the capital city and showed deep care and warm solicitude for the construction of the hospital. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called upon the officials and employees of the hospital to bring about a new turn in preventive and curative work and thus give full play to the advantages of the socialist medical system in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the ceremony, the participants looked round the hospital.

Reception Given in Honor of Woman Boxers 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- The DPRK Cabinet on Tuesday hosted a reception in honor of the woman boxers who proved successful in the 4th World Woman Boxing Championship.
 Present there were Kwak Pom Gi, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Rim Kyong Man, minister of Foreign Trade who is chairman of the Korean Boxing Association, Jong In Chol, vice-chairman of the Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission, and officials in the sports field together with the woman boxers who participated in the championship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kwak Pom Gi in a speech said that the victory of the DPRK boxers in the world woman boxing championship greatly encouraged the army and people in speeding up the building of a great prosperous powerful nation under the banner of great Songun. He called upon the sportsmen and sportswomen to give a good account of themselves at international tournaments to fly the flag of the DPRK in the sky of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Woman boxer Ri Jong Hyang said in reply that they would train themselves more energetically to demonstrate the honor of sportswomen of Songun Korea.

Minju Joson on Base Act of Japan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- Some time ago, the International Organization of Migration (IOM) announced that Germany would finish its payment of compensation to 119,000 survivors from forced labor and slave labor by the end of this year. The payment has been pushed forward from 2000.
 In this regard, Minju Joson Wednesday runs a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan should have made up its mind to liquidate its past earlier than Germany, the commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has not yet made a bold decision to compensate for its inhumane crimes till Germany finishes its liquidation of the past crimes. Far from making compensation, Japan has not even admitted them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This clearly shows the narrow-minded view of Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan seemed very "brave" when it committed such hideous crimes against humanity as unimaginable crimes related to "comfort women" for the Imperial Japanese Army. However, it is so coward in handling the issue of settling its past crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan looks so shabby when compared with what Germany has done so far. Nevertheless, Japan is ridiculously coveting a responsible post at the UNSC. Such an act can be done only by a political dwarf. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan should clearly know this. Germany is by no means inferior to Japan when it has begun redressing its past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With such narrow-mindedness Japan can hardly become full-fledged member of the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This means that unless Japan makes up its mind it will be isolated from the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan would be well advised to have a right choice.

U.S. Veto on Anti-Israel Resolution under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- A resolution denouncing the massacre committed by Israel against Palestinian civilians was turned down at the UNSC due to the U.S. exercise of veto. This is an undisguised act of supporting and defending Israel's brutal killings and an application of unfair double standards in dealing with the human rights issue.
 Rodong Sinmun Wednesday observes this in a signed commentary. This once again fully disclosed the despicable nature of the U.S. as the worst human rights abuser, the commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. behavior indicates that though the U.S. claims it stands for the peace and stability in the Middle East it, in actuality, has only encouraged Israel in the moves to expand its territory and abuse the rights of the Arab people, while aggravating the situation in the Mideast and seeking its despicable strategic interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people in the region are responsible for the settlement of the Mideast issue. The justifiable efforts of the Arab countries to find a fair and comprehensive solution to the Mideast issue are supported by the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Israel should immediately stop its military strikes at Palestine and massacre of civilians and withdraw its aggressor armed forces from all the occupied Arab territories as early as possible as unanimously demanded by the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should halt defending and encouraging Israel in its criminal acts against the Arab world including Palestine.

Suppression of People's Struggle in S. Korea Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- The deputy spokesman for the Democratic Labor Party of south Korea reportedly made public a commentary on Nov. 24 denouncing the "government" for its crackdown upon the participants in the Nov. 22 general turnout of people.
 The "government" took the stand of "no leniency and compromise" with the participants in the general turnout, having no measure for dissolving its conflict with the people over the conclusion of the south Korea-U.S. "Free Trade Agreement," the commentary said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Still more preposterous is the threat of some ministers to "take a strict measure" against the people demanding dialogue with the authorities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This stance of the "government" means violence and arrogance toward the people, noted the commentary.

Open Questionnaire to GNP
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- The Information Department of the Central Committee of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front published an open questionnaire to the Grand National Party of south Korea on Nov. 27, according to the Internet site of Kuguk Jonson.
 The questionnaire says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Bitterly denouncing in the name of all the people the dastardly acts of the GNP in resorting to confrontation, following the lead of outsiders in disregard of the nation's dignity and security and the country's peace and reunification, the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front publishes the following open questionnaire: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Aren't its outcries over "threat from the north" a veil to conceal the threat of the United States to invade the north? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Isn't its advertisement of "unrest of security" over the north's war deterrent for self-defense aimed at inciting hostile feelings against the north by stimulating the psychology of the people? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Isn't its call for an overall discontinuation of dialogue and cooperation with the north intended to reduce the June 15 joint declaration to a dead letter and drive the inter-Korean relations to a total catastrophe? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Isn't its threat that it "does not rule out a war" intended to impose a nuclear holocaust upon all the fellow countrymen and turn the whole land of three thousand ri into debris? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It should not evade answers to our open questions reflecting the will of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  There is no future for the GNP traitors who are piling up hideous treacherous crimes and a stern judgment by history is waiting for them, concludes the questionnaire.

Just Cause of Palestinian People Supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson Wednesday dedicates an article to the "Day of International Solidarity with the Palestinian People." It is the legitimate right of the Palestinian people to regain its usurped territory and establish an independent state and it is a just and sacred cause to struggle for them, the article notes, and goes on:
 On this occasion the Korean people extend firm solidarity to the Palestinian people in their positive struggle to take back the territories usurped by the Israeli aggressors and set up a fully legitimate independent state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Palestinian people expressed their unshakable will not to cease their struggle till they have regained all the occupied territories including the West Bank and Kuds and established the Palestinian independent state, while rejecting and denouncing the anti-Palestine moves of the U.S. imperialists and Israel. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people positively support the Palestinian people in their just cause of winning their national rights and establishing an independent state and bitterly condemn the anti-Palestine moves of Israel. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They will as always stand by the Palestinian people and fully support their just cause.

Foodstuff Production Bases Renovated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- A work for improving the dietary life of the people has been positively pushed ahead with in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Scores of essential foodstuff production bases have been renovated on an expansion basis in recent years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ho Thae Gwon, vice-minister of the Light Industry, told KCNA that the reconstruction project has been carried out by the method of setting model units and generalizing their experiences and thus many successes made in this work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Each province has built essential foodstuff production factories to meet the demand of its people in conformity with its actual conditions with main emphasis laid on the reconstruction of light industrial factories in close contact with the Ministry of Light Industry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Some time ago, a large essential foodstuff factory was built in Paechon County, South Hwanghae Province. It produces various kinds of foodstuffs by making use of hot-spring water, not relying on coal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A technical innovation emulation has been held among essential foodstuff factories throughout the country under the sponsorship of the Central Committee of the Korean General Federation of Science and Technology this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The emulation has put stress on carrying out the prospective targets for the technical innovation of the production processes already set up at each factory. More than hundreds of scientific and technological inventions have been introduced into production during the emulation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There were also lectures on new technologies, video shows and the meetings for exchanging experience during the National Foodstuff Exhibition held in late October.

Zinc Production Process Pays Off
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- A sulfuric acid calcinating production process, an important process of zinc production, has been put under an automatic control system at the Tanchon Smeltery some time ago.
 This is a comprehensive automatic control system which operates by computer the ever-changing production and technical conditions such as temperature, blast volume and charging volume of concentrated ore. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The computerization has made it possible to considerably raise the quality of products as well as to increase production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also raised the sintering ore rate and converted the harmful process into a harmless one, thus doing away with the environmental pollution and saving lots of manpower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The zinc produced by the smeltery enjoys popularity at home and abroad for its quality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now the smeltery, basing itself on the success, is engrossed in establishing an integrated automatic control system of all the other production processes including electrolysis.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Women's Company
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected a Three-Revolution Red Flag women's company of KPA Unit 1174 honored with the title of O Jung Hup-led 7th regiment.
 He watched soldiers' training after acquainting himself with the company's performance of duty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be fulfilled by the company to boost its combat capability, satisfied to learn that the women soldiers are preparing themselves to be a-match-for-a hundred fighters with the pride of holding arms in the era of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Learning about how the company is fulfilling its training program, he underscored the need to conduct effective training to suit its specific conditions to let all the soldiers get well versed in combat and technical equipment and acquire high combat capability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he moved on to an education room, bedroom, mess hall, wash-cum-bath house, non-staple food store, outdoor rest place, barn and other places before enjoying an optimistic art performance given by women soldiers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He met Jon Ok Gyong, company political instructor, whom he got acquainted with a few years ago on his way of field inspection. He learned about what she has done since then and highly praised her for successfully performing her duty as a competent political cadre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly estimated the achievements made by the company in the past, noting that it is a model in all aspects such as efforts to boost the combat capacity, unit management and mass cultural and art activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave servicepersons of the company a pair of binoculars and an automatic rifle as gifts and had a photo session with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Unit 1324
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 29 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected KPA Unit 1324.
 He saw the records showing the victorious and proud path covered by the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the exploits performed by the unit, noting that it is the unit of merits as it fully demonstrated the heroic stamina of the KPA in the defence of the country and the socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He learned about the unit's performance of duty before watching soldiers' training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be undertaken to increase the combat capability of the unit in every way, expressing great satisfaction over the fact that it has firmly equipped its servicepersons with the WPK's Juche-oriented combat methods by building good facilities for training and organizing intensive combat and political training and that as a result, they are performing their duties with a high degree of revolutionary vigilance and in a responsible manner, always keeping themselves combat-ready. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round a general lecture room, education room, video room and other entertainment and educational facilities, he learned about how political work is conducted among the servicepersons of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the units of the KPA are conducting energetic information and agitation activities full of militancy and enthusiasm, imbuing the servicepersons with the fighting spirit, he said, adding that political and ideological work is a central point to be held fast to by the KPA, an army strong in ideology and faith. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took deep care of the soldiers' living, going round facilities for supply service. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He highly praised the unit's commanding officers for valuing and taking deep care of their soldiers as their real brothers and sisters would do, pleased to learn that the unit has made thorough-going preparations for wintering so that they may spend winter in warm rooms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA soldiers are assiduously managing their economic life by their own efforts though they are stationed in the very unfavorable area, he said, adding that the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance and fortitude displayed by the KPA serves as a powerful engine dynamically advancing the times and the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave the servicepersons of the unit a pair of binoculars and an automatic rifle as gifts and had a photo session with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong and Vice Department Director of the C.C., WPK Hwang Pyong So.
